1(1!) + 2(2!) + \cdot \cdot \cdot +n(n!) = (n+1)!-1
(1)(1!) = (1+1)!-1
1 = (2\cdot1)-1
1 = 1 \checkmark
1(1!) + 2(2!) + \cdot \cdot \cdot +k(k!) = (k+1)!-1
1(1!) + 2(2!) + \cdot \cdot \cdot +(k+1)(k+1)! = (k+2)!-1
\big[RHS\big]
(k+2)!-1 = (k+2)(k+1)k!-1
\big[LHS\big]
=\underbrace{1(1!) + 2(2!) + \cdot \cdot \cdot + k(k+1)!} + (k+1)(k+1)!
= \underbrace{(k+1)!-1}+(k+1)(k+1)!
= (k+1)!-1 + (k+1)(k+1)k!
= (k+1)k!-1 + (k+1)^{2}k!
 = (k+1)k! + (k+1)^2k! -1 
 = (k+1)(k!)(1 + (k+1))-1
 = (k+1)(k!)(k+2)-1 = (k+2)(k+1)k!-1
(k+1)k! - 1 + (k+1)^2 k!
